The paper deals with data privacy concerns in system logs and proposes a novel approach for anonymization using collision-resistant hashing algorithms. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the challenge of balancing data usefulness and privacy preservation, which relates to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and software engineering (cs.SE). The metric introduced to assess data usefulness for failure analysis involves machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes a method for irreversible encoding of system logs, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL).
